To promote togetherness and solidarity in Africa, a musical festival tagged, Africa Reggae and Dance Fest is set to take place on March 28, 2020 in Lagos. The event which is put together by Nigerian reggae-dancehall Patoranking is aim to amplify the voice of the African Spirit while strengthening the continent’s position and image through music. According to him, the show will feature a highly curated selection of artistes both local and international where attendees will be immerse in music, dance and a cultural experience like no other. “I have always wanted to bring this experience to the continent, now is the right time and what best way than to start in Lagos where I am from,” said Patoranking. “With events usually held towards the end of the year during the festive period, ARDF is more than a festival and in hopes of raising the festival bar in Africa, it will be known for its distinctive cultural experience and its world class performances set to unite music fans.” As one of the most celebrated brands in music and having achieved extraordinary success, Patoranking values excellence, unity and is committed to bringing out the best in arts and culture.